  "body": [
    "Bhai Bhagwant Singh Ji was the younger brother of Bhai Angad Singh Ji, who was popularly known as ‘Reetan Da Baadshah’. Bhai Bhagwant Singh Ji was born on 10th October 1933 in the city of Gujranwala, which is now in Pakistan. Following the partition of Punjab in 1947, their family moved to Delhi, where he performed Kirtan with Bhai Angad Singh Ji. Sometime in the 1970s, Bhai Bhagwant Singh Ji migrated to the United Kingdom and served as the Head Granthi in Central Gurdwara (Khalsa Jatha) London. He was also a committee member of the Gurdwara from 2006 to 2020 and served as the President of the Gurdwara Sahib from 2006 to 2010. Bhai Bhagwant Singh Ji took his last breath and left for his heavenly abode on 31st March 2020 after sustaining a head injury from a prior fall. If anyone has more information or recordings of Bhai Bhagwant Singh Ji to share, please contact us."
